 CROSS-SECTION EVALUATION PROCEDURE                               7431 1451
                                                                  7431 1451
 Adopted procedure is based on careful theoretical                7431 1451
 analysis utilizing available experimental data and               7431 1451
 nuclear reaction model calculations.                             7431 1451
                                                                  7431 1451
 Available experimental data were interpreted  using              7431 1451
 nuclear reaction model code EMPIRE-2.19b35 by                    7431 1451
 M. Herman et al [He01, He02]. This code integrates               7431 1451
 into a single system a number of important modules               7431 1451
 and features:                                                    7431 1451
                                                                  7431 1451
 - Spherical and deformed Optical Model including                 7431 1451
   coupled-channels (ECIS03 by J. Raynal)                         7431 1451
 - Hauser-Feshbach statistical model including                    7431 1451
   HRTW width fluctuation correction                              7431 1451
 - Quantum-mechanical MSD TUL model (codes ORION &                7431 1451
   TRISTAN by H. Lenske), and MSC NVWY model                      7431 1451
 - Exciton model with angular momentum coupling                   7431 1451
   (code DEGAS by E. Betak and P. Oblozinsky) that                7431 1451
   represents a good approximation to the DSD model               7431 1451
 - Exciton model with Iwamoto-Harada cluster                      7431 1451
   emission and Kalbach systematic angular distr.                 7431 1451
   (code PCROSS by R.Capote et al)                                7431 1451
 - Complete gamma-ray cascade after emission of                   7431 1451
   each particle, including realistic treatment of                7431 1451
   discrete transitions                                           7431 1451
 - Access to OM segment of the RIPL-2 library [Ri03]              7431 1451
 - Built-in input parameter files, such as masses,                7431 1451
   level density, discrete levels, fission barriers               7431 1451
   and gamma strength functions  based on the RIPL-2              7431 1451
   library [Ri03]                                                 7431 1451
 - Automatic retrieval of experimental data from the              7431 1451
   EXFOR/CSISRS library                                           7431 1451
 - ENDF-6 formatting (code EMPEND by A. Trkov)                    7431 1451
   coupled to graphical presentation capabilities                 7431 1451
   (code ZVView by V. Zerkin) through the chain of                7431 1451
   PrePro codes by R. Cullen                                      7431 1451
 - Checking codes (CHECKR, FIZCON, PSYCHE)                        7431 1451
 - Support for NJOY                                               7431 1451
