RESONANCE COVARIANCE DATA (L. Leal, ORNL, Jan 2008)               7431 1451
                                                                  7431 1451
The procedure used to generate the resolved covariance data       7431 1451
with the SAMMY code is as follow:                                 7431 1451
 a) Retrieve best set of available resonance parameters.          7431 1451
 b) Convert the resonance parameters into the Reich-Moore form.   7431 1451
 c) Generate "experimental" cross sections for total, scattering, 7431 1451
    and capture cross sections with the NJOY code, for use as     7431 1451
    "experimental data" in SAMMY.                                 7431 1451
 d) Assign a global "experimental" uncertainty to the             7431 1451
    "experimental data." The uncertainties used were based on     7431 1451
    uncertainty in the thermal capture cross section and          7431 1451
    uncertainty in the capture resonance integrals.               7431 1451
 e) Run SAMMY code with the option to generate                    7431 1451
    resonance-covariances retroactively.                          7431 1451
 f) Convert the resonance-covariance results from SAMMY into      7431 1451
    the ENDF format for file 32 and MT=151.                       7431 1451
                                                                  7431 1451
The resulting resonance parameters and covariance were used in    7431 1451
the calculations of average cross sections and uncertainties.     7431 1451
The calculations were done with SAMMY, ERRORJ, and PUFF-IV codes. 7431 1451
The results of these three codes agreed very well.                7431 1451
